'''Yamato no Tehiko''' (year of birth and death unknown ) was a {{ill|Gōzoku|lt=powerful|en|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōzoku|qq=}} clan leader in [[Kofun period|the Kofun period]] and one of '''[[Yamato no Kuni no Miyatsuko|the Yamato kuni no miyatsuko]]''' . His Kabane was {{ill|10=ja|11=直 (姓)|Atai|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}}

He served under [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]] and participated in the Silla war

== Origin ==
The Wa clan (Wa koku no [[Yamato no Kuni no Miyatsuko|miyatsuko family]] ) was a powerful clan in [[Yamato Province|Yamato-go]], Joka - gun, Yamato Province, which currently corresponds to Yamato, Saho-cho, in the southern part of [[Tenri, Nara|Tenri City]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]] . The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=}} 's "Yamato no Kuni Kamiwake" section states that "his descendants were Kamichitsuhiko no Mikoto," while [[Nihon Shoki|the Nihon Shoki]], Volume 3 states that his ancestor was {{ill|Saonetsuhiko|lt=Shiinetsuhiko|fr|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saonetsuhiko|qq=}} <ref>『日本書紀』神武天皇即位前紀甲寅年10月5日条</ref>, and the [[Kojiki]] states that his ancestor was {{ill|Saonetsuhiko|fr|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saonetsuhiko|qq=}} <ref>『古事記』中巻、神武天皇条</ref> .
{{Short description|Japanese noble family|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

